data.title: Daily blog from Bondi Beach — Morning Bondi
data.meta_description: Daily dose of Bondi Beach by Morning Bondi, a photographer who's been taking photos of the iconic beach of Bondi since 2011. The photos cover the sunrise, the famous Icebergs pool, the Bondi to Coogee coastal walk, the usual Bondi residents and anything else that happens in the morning.
data.text:
Morning gang,

How's everyone doing?

This morning I was awake by 4:20 am, don't ask me why but it's definitely not the time I set up the alarm clock for.

I only see a few explanations, our basketball win from last night? (The 'Bondi Hoop Troop', remember that name, one day we might be famous) My trip to France tomorrow? No idea but ehh I won't complain as I was able to see the first lights over Bronte.

Maaaaate, it was unreal. The pink hues all over the bay were stunning. The sunrise was not bad either. I snapped like a maniac then I finished with a dip in the pool. Gosh, it was cold!

The perfect morning before a hiatus of 6 weeks. That's right, don't expect anything from me for all that time. I will be in Europe enjoying the warm weather.

In the meantime, look after yourself and chat on my return in mid-August.

Lots of love,

Xoxo

Amo

Morning team,

How’s everyone today? Another day, another cracker…

This time of the year can be extraordinary from a light point of view and today didn’t disappoint. I went to my usual spots (yep, I’m a creature of habit) and I just had to point and shoot. It was looking good from all the angles.

I bumped into a few of my morning friends, quick chats, coffee, photos, dip and back home. Life is good.

Have a wonderful day my friends,

Xoxo

Amo

Morning team,

How’s everyone today? Great weekend?

This morning was cold (as the past few weeks) but outstanding morning. The light was incredible, the water divine (yeah I know I’m amongst the crazy ones that still go for dips in the morning) and a seal was hanging out in North Bondi. Nah, not in the water, just on Ramp 6.

What a great seal-abration for my last week in Bondi for a little while… I’m flying to France for 6-weeks. Yep, lucky me - skipping a good portion of winter. I guess that’s the perks of having your own business, you can work from anywhere! ;)

Have a lovely week my friends,

Xoxo

Morning team,

How’s everyone today? Freezing? Fair enough, it was 5°C around 6 AM. I’m not going to lie, I can’t wait to board my plane to Europe in a bit more than a week.

Besides the cold temperature, it was a glorious morning. The first lights were on point, the sunrise glorious, the waves decent and heaps more people around, including a few of my mates.

I’m not going to lie, I don’t have much to say today so will leave you with this.

Have a wonderful day my friends and as I won’t be able to come down tomorrow morning, chat with you on Monday.

Xoxo

Amo

Morning gang,

How good was this morning!

The horizon line was clear which means the sun popped up earlier than the past few days. The surf was still big but dropped a little. The only downside was probably the chilly breeze which means there were not that many people swimming. If you went in, like I did, chances are that I have a photo of you.

Today is going to be pretty chilled, a bit of work than lunch planned with the Zambrero team to celebrate our partnership and all the latest campaigns that we cooked together. By the way, if you haven't seen it yet, Dom Littrich (aka Spicy Meatball) just released a 🌶️ banger to launch the new Spicy range at Zam. What do we think? Worth entering the GRAMMYs?

Have a wonderful day my friends and chat tomorrow,

Xoxo

Amo

Hola gang,

How's everyone doing? Great weekend?

Mine was busy but excellent. Ian Darling from Shark Island Productions and his team kindly invited me to watch the new doco called ‘The Pool’. It's about the iconic Bondi Icebergs pool and all the different communities gravitating around it.

If you are as obsessed as I am about the Icebergs, I strongly recommend you watch the film, it's 1.5 hours of pure goodness. So many familiar faces are featured too.

The Icebergs is the most photographed pool in the world. No shit! (excuse my French) I probably take at least 10 photos per day and I have been doing so for the past 14 years which means that I have at least 50,000+ images of the Icebergs, I’m not even kidding.

Here are some of my favourite ones. I have pretty much every angle covered, even the most controversial ones taken in the pool - it's not allowed but Frenchies are not great with rules, but you already know that. If you want to see more photos, check out my special Icebergs gallery page.

Have a wonderful week my friends,

Xoxo

Amo

PS: If you are not following @bread_agency yet, you should. Last week was a big one, we announced the appointment of 6 new team members (that makes nine of us now). BAM! We are ready to roll... 🍞🚀🤩

Morning team,

I hope you’ve all been well. My apologies for the radio silence but between the funny weather, my week in Cairns last week for the ‘Cannes in Cairns’ conference (highly recommend it) and pure laziness (let’s be honest for a sec), it’s been a while.

I know people might think I’ve made a typo on the title ‘Where’s Willy?’ No, it’s, unfortunately, not! It was freezing cold down there and yes I still went for a swim because why not? Surprisingly, the water was warmer than out there. Heaps of whales at the back too.

Besides this, not much to photograph today. I tried to get creative but ain’t that easy when there are not many photo subjects. My advice to you. If you’ve ever dreamt of being featured on Morning Bondi or good mate Aquabumps, come down for a swim, surf or even a chat with us and chances are you will get a feature. We need photo subjects. It’s boring AF when there is no one around.

On that note, love to you all and chat tomorrow.

Xoxo

Amo

Morning gang,

How’s everyone this morning?

It was such a lovely morning down there but gosh it was cold. That breeze was not so pleasant.

I caught up with good friend Caroline for sunrise in the South End, of course. The reflection on the sand was just so good and I’m a sucker for this.

Whales, they are back in town and we saw two cruising around. Love this time of the year!

Have a cracking day and remember that I won’t be able to take photos tomorrow and Thursday.

Xoxo

Amo

Morning my friends,

How’s everyone this morning? How was your weekend?

Another morning, another cracker, after weeks of rain, we now have weeks of sunshine and pretty good waves, love it!

I went down to my usual spots to capture a few photos. Yes, I’m a creature of habits. I love the South corner better than the north end and the view above the Icebergs is pretty special.

Have a fantastic week my friends. I will go down tomorrow but be warned I won’t go on Wednesday and Thursday as I’m in Avalon for a Bread shoot. Yeah, all good I have my passport ready.

Xoxo

Amo

Morning gang,

How's everyone today?!

Everything was absolutely brilliant but gosh that cold wind was harsh. I was cold the whole morning and because I like to suffer even more, I finished with a dip in the ocean. The water temperature is pretty good but that cold breeze is not so pleasant afterwards. Let's not even talk about the cold shower afterwards... the pipes must be frozen.

Other than this, I’ve had a great week. Hope you had a good one too. My highlight was a talk I attended last night at Mumbrella 360 about the Shift 20 initiative. I rarely do LinkedIn posts like that but I found Dylan Alcott and Sara Shams' childhood stories pretty heartbreaking. As I know 77% of people in Bondi are working in Creative, Advertising or Marketing (don’t quote me on that one, I pulled that stat out of my 🍑), I thought I should share it here too. We can make that shift. Let’s do it!

On that note, have a cracking weekend and chat next week.

Xoxo

Amo

PS: Last, but not least. Thank you so much for all your input on my last post. Most of you read my daily rambling and I love you even more for that. You bloody legends! 😍

Morning gang,

How's everyone doing? I asked this same question pretty much every day but rarely anyone respond. Do you even read captions?

Let's do a test with some old-school Lorem ipsum-generated text and see what happens.

Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Sed at pellentesque arcu, sed congue felis. Vivamus efficitur volutpat nunc ut tincidunt. Quisque gravida facilisis blandit. Suspendisse egestas at nulla nec consequat. Proin eu dolor orci. Vestibulum accumsan placerat dolor, vel ultricies ligula placerat vel. Proin euismod mauris at mi efficitur sollicitudin.

Comment down below if you actually read my posts or if you are only here for the photos. I won't blame you if that's the case. It will just save me a fair bit of my time. Writing new 💩 every day about the same beach ain't that simple.

Xoxo

Amo

Morning my friends,

My apologies for the radio silence but between the rain and work, I haven't had much chance to go down to take photos.

Hope you've been well and all had a good weekend.

Mine was excellent, thanks for asking. We went down to Berry and stayed at the best Airbnb I've ever been called Jasper Valley House. Don't look any further if you are heading that way. The owners Glynn and Nicky are absolute legends and thought about literally everything.

This morning was gorgeous with some nice waves rolling and I bumped into a few local legends but gosh it was freezing. Yeah, I still went for a dip as it's still the best way to wake up but the run from the ocean to the shower wasn't pleasant.

Have a wonderful week ahead and stay warm.

Xoxo

Amo

Morning my friends,

What an incredible morning down in Paradiseland!

I ventured down the beach before sunrise to witness the amazing paddle out organised by all the clubs around for the victims who lost their lives in Bondi Junction. It was the perfect morning for it and it was lovely to see all the different communities rallying together for this.

The sunrise was a cracker, the waves big and a lot of surfers making the most of them. The light was on point and I bumped into all my beach mates.

On another note, if you are ever interested in knowing more about what I do for work with 🍞, check this lovely article organised by Greg Graham aka 'Sparrow' and the B&T team. Thanks for your support guys! 🙌🏼

Enjoy your day team,

Xoxo

Amo

Morning gang,

How was your weekend? Any good?

This morning started pretty well. I was in North Bondi (NoBo for the hipsters).

Started by exercising with the training crew and had to stop when the sun popped up. Nice light but not much going on. I snapped whatever was in front of me. You know there is not much to photograph when I take photos of birds (talking about cockatoos here).

Have a fabulous day my friends and a great week!

Ciao,

Amo

Morning gang,

Hope you've all had a great week and you are ready for the weekend.

This morning was pretty special.

The entire of Bondi was farewelling ex-Olympian swimmer and Coach Neil Rogers, a true local legend. If you don't know him, you would have seen him at the Icebergs every Friday or on the sand in North Bondi. He was a very special man and I'm certainly going to miss not seeing him around the edge of the pool and hearing his voice. All my condolences to the entire Bondi community and his family and friends. Bon vent mon ami ! 💔

The sun was shining for him, the pool had a new fresh coat of paint for him too and all his swim squad group was having a moment.

I was with Em who was keen to experience what a Morning Bondi sesh was all about. Let's be honest, it's the best routine, wake up with the sun, coffee and swim. The photos are here to capture what's happening around us.

Have a fabulous Friday and cherish your time with your loved ones, life is precious.

Xoxo

Amo

Morning my friends,

Hope you're all well.

This morning, I went for a Bondi to Tamarama walk along the coastline with good mate Simon. Gorgeous sunrise, perfect temperatures outside and inside the water. Highly recommend it. Hope you had a great morning.

Finally, I just wanted to acknowledge what happened on Saturday in Bondi Junction. I was away for the weekend with no phone reception. It was only when we were driving back yesterday afternoon that we discovered all the atrocities. My condolences to all the family and friends who lost a loved one. Take care of yourself and stay strong!

Lots of love,

Xoxo

Amo

Morning gang,

Hope you are all well and had a good weekend.

How good was the weather! So unexpected after last Friday's pouring rain.

Daylight saving is ON or OFF, I'm not sure what you are meant to say but basically, we changed the time yesterday which means that the sunrise is one hour earlier than last week which is perfect.

I woke up at 5:20 am and was down the beach by 6 am for coffee, photos and a dip in the ocean. Yes, it takes me a good 40 mins to look that good in the morning (jokes!).

The sunrise was fab and the surf was hectic. I always finish with a dip in the ocean - I call this "tea-bagging" I will leave you with this wonderful image.

Enjoy your week my friends,

Xoxo

Amo

Morning my friends,

Hope you've all had a great weekend. What a lovely start to the week!

When I arrived at the beach, I could tell that it was going to be a nice one and guess what it didn't disappoint for a second.

Pink clouds and golden light for the win. There were a fair bit of people making the most of their mornings.

I started in South Bondi and finished in North to join my mates. North was nice but South still wins.

Have a lovely week my friends!

Xoxo

Amo

Morning my friends,

Hope you are all well and ready to win the day.

This morning for a change of scenery, I ventured to my second favourite beach of the East, Bronte.

Started by the pool and finished with the Authenticity Ice Bath gang.

Alex Ross from Authenticity is an absolute legend and organises ice bath sessions every week for FREE. Yep, that’s this type of guy who loves to give back to the community. Saying this, he’s currently looking for a brand sponsor to help him and the charity he’s partnering with to pay for the ice. So if you are a marketer and sitting on a pile of cash and don’t know what to do with it, please reach out to him. He’s not asking for much. In exchange, you can brand his ice buckets and he can organise tailored events for your company. Go nuts! He deserves it.

On another note, unless you are following me or Bread on LinkedIn, you might not be aware that we are now looking for another Social Account Director to join the 🍞 team. Yep, we went BIG this time and splashed our entire recruitment budget on that sign but finding the best candidate for the job is worth it.

Have a cracking day my friends and chat with you on Friday,

Xoxo

Amo
